INSERT INTO `books` VALUES (1,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/81EcXiV-9WL._SL1500_.jpg','Crime and Punishment','Fyodor Dostoevsky',11.99,'Raskolnikov, an impoverished student tormented by his own nihilism, and the struggle between good and evil, believes he is above the law. Convinced that humanitarian ends justify vile means, he brutally murders an old woman—a pawnbroker whom he regards as stupid, ailing, greedy…good for nothing. Overwhelmed afterward by feelings of guilt and terror, Raskolnikov confesses to the crime and goes to prison. There he realizes that happiness and redemption can only be achieved through suffering.','book','Dover Publications; Reprint edition','2001-08-22','English',430,300),(2,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/81aY1lxk+9L._SL1500_.jpg','To Kill a Mockingbird','Harper Lee',7.99,'Set in the racially charged atmosphere of Alabama in the 1930s, this Pulitzer Prize-winning novel follows young Scout Finch and her brother Jem as they navigate the moral and social complexities of their small town, guided by their father, lawyer Atticus Finch, who is defending a black man falsely accused of raping a white woman.','book','Harper Perennial Modern Classics; Reprint edition','2006-07-05','English',336,280),(3,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/71rpa1-kyvL._SL1500_.jpg','1984','George Orwell',9.99,'In a dystopian future where totalitarianism reigns, Winston Smith works for the Ministry of Truth, altering historical records to fit the Party\'s propaganda. As he grows disillusioned with the oppressive regime, he starts a forbidden love affair and begins to rebel against the system, risking everything for freedom.','book','Houghton Mifflin Harcourt; Reprint edition','1990-05-01','English',328,260),(4,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/412bjj40hoL._SY445_SX342_.jpg','Pride and Prejudice','Jane Austen',6.99,'This classic novel of manners explores the courtship rituals of the British gentry of the early 19th century. Elizabeth Bennet, intelligent and spirited, navigates her way through society\'s expectations and her own prejudices as she falls in love with the proud but honorable Mr. Darcy.','book','Penguin Classics; Reprint edition','2002-12-31','English',279,240),(5,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/61dRoDRubtL._SL1500_.jpg','The Great Gatsby','F. Scott Fitzgerald',10.99,'In this quintessential tale of the Roaring Twenties, the mysterious and wealthy Jay Gatsby throws lavish parties at his Long Island mansion. Narrator Nick Carraway becomes entangled in Gatsby\'s obsession with the beautiful Daisy Buchanan, leading to tragedy and a reflection on the American Dream.','book','Scribner; Reprint edition','2004-09-30','English',180,200),(6,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/91PBkjTNJhL._SL1500_.jpg','Moby Dick','Herman Melville',8.99,'Captain Ahab is obsessed with killing Moby Dick, the great white whale that maimed him. This epic tale of revenge, obsession, and the struggle against nature explores the limits of human knowledge and the depths of human madness.','book','Penguin Classics; Reprint edition','2001-10-18','English',720,540),(7,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/81zE42gT3xL._SL1500_.jpg','Brave New World','Aldous Huxley',9.49,'In a futuristic world where humanity is controlled by technology and conditioned to accept their roles in society, Bernard Marx begins to question the rigid system that suppresses individuality and freedom. His journey exposes the dark underbelly of a seemingly perfect society.','book','Harper Perennial Modern Classics; Reprint edition','2006-10-17','English',288,220),(8,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/8125BDk3l9L._SL1500_.jpg','The Catcher in the Rye','J.D. Salinger',7.49,'Holden Caulfield, a teenager from New York City, recounts his days following his expulsion from an elite boarding school. Through his cynical and sensitive lens, he explores themes of identity, belonging, and alienation in a world he feels disconnected from.','book','Little, Brown and Company; Reprint edition','2001-01-30','English',277,220),(9,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/81pwJjgcwwL._SL1500_.jpg','Jane Eyre','Charlotte Brontë',8.49,'Orphaned and mistreated by her aunt and cousins, Jane Eyre endures a harsh education at Lowood School before becoming a governess at Thornfield Hall. There, she meets the enigmatic Mr. Rochester and discovers dark secrets that test her moral and emotional resilience.','book','Penguin Classics; Reprint edition','2002-12-31','English',624,500),(10,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/81ioPZFMeUL._SL1500_.jpg','The Alchemist','Paulo Coelho',9.99,'Santiago, a shepherd boy, dreams of finding a worldly treasure and sets off on a journey to the Egyptian pyramids. Along the way, he learns about the spiritual insights that are more valuable than material riches. This allegorical novel is a tale of self-discovery and the pursuit of one\'s personal legend.','book','HarperOne; Reprint edition','1993-05-01','English',208,200),(11,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/712cDO7d73L._SL1500_.jpg','The Hobbit','J.R.R. Tolkien',10.99,'Bilbo Baggins, a hobbit, is swept into an epic quest to reclaim the lost Dwarf Kingdom of Erebor from the fearsome dragon Smaug. Guided by Gandalf the wizard and thirteen dwarves, Bilbo\'s journey takes him into the wild, to the Lonely Mountain, and into the history books.','book','Mariner Books; Reprint edition','2012-09-18','English',320,400),(12,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/81nV6x2ey4L._SL1500_.jpg','The Lord of the Rings','J.R.R. Tolkien',15.99,'An epic high-fantasy novel, it follows the quest to destroy the One Ring, forged by the Dark Lord Sauron, and save Middle-earth from his clutches. The Fellowship of the Ring, the Two Towers, and the Return of the King detail the journey of hobbits, elves, dwarves, and men.','book','Houghton Mifflin Harcourt; Reprint edition','2005-10-12','English',1216,1250),(13,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/91wKDODkgWL._SL1500_.jpg','Harry Potter and the Sorcerer\'s Stone','J.K. Rowling',12.99,'Harry Potter discovers on his eleventh birthday that he is the orphaned son of two powerful wizards and possesses unique magical powers of his own. He is summoned from his life as an unwanted child to become a student at Hogwarts, an English boarding school for wizards.','book','Scholastic; Reprint edition','1998-09-01','English',309,350),(14,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/918wxhKJaPL._SL1500_.jpg','Harry Potter and the Chamber of Secrets','J.K. Rowling',12.99,'Harry Potter returns to Hogwarts School of Witchcraft and Wizardry for his second year to discover the school plagued by mysterious attacks and sinister messages written in blood.','book','Scholastic; Reprint edition','1999-06-02','English',341,370),(15,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/812CcFkEPCL._SL1200_.jpg','Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban','J.K. Rowling',12.99,'Harry Potter\'s third year at Hogwarts is packed with more danger and adventure as he learns that a dangerous convict, Sirius Black, has escaped from the wizard prison, Azkaban, and is bent on finding him.','book','Scholastic; Reprint edition','1999-09-08','English',435,410),(16,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/91-LL7OnDCL._SL1500_.jpg','Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire','J.K. Rowling',13.99,'Harry Potter\'s fourth year at Hogwarts is filled with even more danger as he unexpectedly finds himself entered into the Triwizard Tournament, a grueling magical competition with other wizarding schools.','book','Scholastic; Reprint edition','2000-07-08','English',734,780),(17,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/71pgI2ou5oL._SL1200_.jpg','Harry Potter and the Order of the Phoenix','J.K. Rowling',14.99,'In Harry Potter\'s fifth year at Hogwarts, he faces the worst Defense Against the Dark Arts teacher yet, new regulations from the Ministry of Magic, and growing opposition from those who refuse to believe Voldemort has returned.','book','Scholastic; Reprint edition','2003-06-21','English',870,820),(18,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/61sXBXmAWML._SL1000_.jpg','Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince','J.K. Rowling',13.99,'As Harry Potter begins his sixth year at Hogwarts, he discovers an old book marked as \'the property of the Half-Blood Prince\', which helps him excel in Potions class and gives him insight into Lord Voldemort\'s dark past.','book','Scholastic; Reprint edition','2005-07-16','English',652,720),(19,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/91VsRHjTY-L._SL1500_.jpg','Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows','J.K. Rowling',14.99,'Harry Potter\'s final year at Hogwarts is filled with danger as he and his friends, Ron and Hermione, set out to destroy the Horcruxes that hold pieces of Voldemort\'s soul.','book','Scholastic; Reprint edition','2007-07-21','English',784,850),(20,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/81p86pu0xBL._SL1500_.jpg','The Ride of a Lifetime','Robert Iger',12.99,'Robert Iger shares the lessons he learned during his fifteen years as CEO of The Walt Disney Company, offering insights on leadership and business strategy.','book','Random House; Reprint edition','2019-09-23','English',272,260),(21,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/811nqCf7o1L._SL1500_.jpg','The Da Vinci Code','Dan Brown',9.99,'Harvard symbologist Robert Langdon and cryptologist Sophie Neveu unravel a series of codes and puzzles while investigating a murder in the Louvre, uncovering a conspiracy that could shake the foundations of Christianity.','book','Anchor; Reprint edition','2006-03-28','English',489,520),(22,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/61LKD6scbfL._SL1500_.jpg','Principles: Life and Work','Ray Dalio',14.99,'Ray Dalio shares the unconventional principles that have guided him in life and work, providing practical advice for achieving success in business and beyond.','book','Simon & Schuster; Reprint edition','2017-09-19','English',592,450),(23,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/914cHl9v7oL._SL1500_.jpg','The Book Thief','Markus Zusak',10.99,'In Nazi Germany, young Liesel Meminger discovers a love for books and shares them with her neighbors during bombing raids as well as with the Jewish man hiding in her basement.','book','Knopf Books for Young Readers; Reprint edition','2007-09-11','English',592,450),(24,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/71un2hI4mcL._SL1500_.jpg','The Hunger Games','Suzanne Collins',8.99,'In a dystopian future, Katniss Everdeen volunteers to take her sister\'s place in the Hunger Games, a televised fight to the death among 24 teenagers, and must navigate the deadly competition while confronting her own humanity.','book','Scholastic Press; Reprint edition','2010-07-03','English',384,320),(25,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/61Gs9LIHu8L._SL1200_.jpg','Catching Fire','Suzanne Collins',9.99,'Katniss Everdeen\'s victory in the Hunger Games sparks a rebellion in the districts of Panem. As she returns for the Quarter Quell, she faces greater challenges, both physical and political.','book','Scholastic Press; Reprint edition','2013-07-03','English',391,340),(26,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/61n5pTMvmpL._SL1200_.jpg','Mockingjay','Suzanne Collins',10.99,'Katniss Everdeen becomes the symbol of a mass rebellion against the autocratic Capitol. As the war escalates, she must determine whom she can trust and what sacrifices she must make for freedom.','book','Scholastic Press; Reprint edition','2014-07-03','English',400,350),(27,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/91oNu+R7EUL._SL1500_.jpg','Divergent','Veronica Roth',9.99,'In a society divided into five factions, each dedicated to a particular virtue, Tris Prior discovers that she is Divergent and will never fit into any one group. As she uncovers a conspiracy to destroy all Divergents, she must learn to trust the mysterious Four and find out what makes being Divergent so dangerous.','book','Katherine Tegen Books; Reprint edition','2012-02-28','English',496,420),(28,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/61cVGcPtvtL._SL1200_.jpg','Insurgent','Veronica Roth',9.99,'One choice can destroy you. Tris Prior\'s initiation day should have been marked by celebration and victory with her chosen faction; instead, the day ended with unspeakable horrors. Now war looms as conflict between the factions and their ideologies grows. And in times of war, sides must be chosen, secrets will emerge, and choices will become even more irrevocable—and even more powerful.','book','Katherine Tegen Books; Reprint edition','2013-10-22','English',592,440),(29,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/81DPjDhnE-L._SL1500_.jpg','Allegiant','Veronica Roth',10.99,'The explosive conclusion to Veronica Roth\'s Divergent trilogy reveals the secrets of the dystopian world. As war surges, Tris and her friends must discover what lies beyond the wall that encloses their city.','book','Katherine Tegen Books; Reprint edition','2014-10-07','English',544,450),(30,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/91Jra1QAMPL._SL1500_.jpg','The Maze Runner','James Dashner',9.99,'Thomas wakes up with no memory in the middle of a maze and realizes he must work with the community of boys to escape. But as they face the horrors of the maze and uncover the secrets of their captivity, they discover that their escape may only be the beginning.','book','Delacorte Press; Reprint edition','2010-08-24','English',375,320),(31,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/71hbDMgo6rL._SL1200_.jpg','The Scorch Trials','James Dashner',9.99,'After escaping the Maze, Thomas and his friends face a new set of trials on the Scorch, a barren, sun-scorched wasteland. As they battle against the elements and each other, they uncover deeper truths about the nature of their world and their role within it.','book','Delacorte Press; Reprint edition','2011-10-11','English',384,330),(32,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/91vaqmbaF4L._SL1500_.jpg','The Death Cure','James Dashner',10.99,'In the conclusion of the Maze Runner series, Thomas and his friends face their most dangerous challenges yet as they attempt to discover the truth about WICKED and find a cure for the Flare.','book','Delacorte Press; Reprint edition','2012-01-08','English',352,310),(33,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/61fbVx3W5cL._SL1200_.jpg','The Fault in Our Stars','John Green',10.99,'Sixteen-year-old Hazel, a cancer patient, meets and falls in love with Augustus, a fellow cancer patient, at a support group. Their story is a heartbreaking and inspiring journey of love, loss, and the eternal impact of a meaningful life.','book','Dutton Books; Reprint edition','2014-04-08','English',313,290),(34,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/7127ZROAw5L._SL1500_.jpg','Looking for Alaska','John Green',9.99,'Miles \'Pudge\' Halter\'s safe life is upended when he meets Alaska Young, a beautiful, clever, and emotionally troubled student at his new boarding school. As he gets drawn into her reckless world, he finds himself exploring the meaning of life and love.','book','Dutton Books; Reprint edition','2005-03-03','English',221,250),(35,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/81WBJQUEFsL._SL1500_.jpg','Paper Towns','John Green',10.99,'Quentin Jacobsen has spent a lifetime loving the magnificent Margo Roth Spiegelman from afar. So when she cracks open a window and climbs back into his life, summoning him for an ingenious campaign of revenge, he follows. But after their all-nighter ends and a new day breaks, Margo has disappeared. Always an enigma, Margo has now become a mystery. But there are clues. And they\'re for Quentin.','book','Dutton Books; Reprint edition','2008-10-16','English',305,280),(36,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/71hnAhliemL._SL1500_.jpg','An Abundance of Katherines','John Green',9.99,'Colin Singleton is a washed-up child prodigy who has dated nineteen girls named Katherine and been dumped by all of them. In the wake of his latest breakup, he takes a road trip with his best friend to prove the Theorem of Underlying Katherine Predictability, which he hopes will predict the future of any relationship.','book','Dutton Books; Reprint edition','2006-09-21','English',227,260),(37,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/615ZIxEDozL._SL1500_.jpg','Twilight','Stephenie Meyer',10.99,'When Bella Swan moves to Forks, Washington, she meets the mysterious and alluring Edward Cullen, who is harboring a dark secret: he\'s a vampire. As their relationship develops, Bella is thrust into the world of the supernatural and faces challenges she never anticipated.','book','Little, Brown and Company; Reprint edition','2005-10-05','English',498,420),(38,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/81KvBJj7cEL._SL1500_.jpg','New Moon','Stephenie Meyer',10.99,'In the second installment of the Twilight Saga, Bella Swan is devastated by the abrupt departure of her vampire love, Edward Cullen, but her spirit is rekindled by her growing friendship with the irresistible Jacob Black. Suddenly, she finds herself drawn into the world of the werewolves, ancestral enemies of the vampires, and finds her loyalties tested.','book','Little, Brown and Company; Reprint edition','2006-09-06','English',563,450),(39,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/71vbRiLnoqL._SL1500_.jpg','Eclipse','Stephenie Meyer',10.99,'As Seattle is ravaged by a string of mysterious killings and a malicious vampire continues her quest for revenge, Bella again finds herself surrounded by danger. In the midst of it all, she is forced to choose between her love for Edward and her friendship with Jacob—knowing that her decision may ignite the ageless struggle between vampire and werewolf.','book','Little, Brown and Company; Reprint edition','2007-08-07','English',640,500),(40,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/71AWYilcOnL._SL1500_.jpg','Breaking Dawn','Stephenie Meyer',12.99,'In the final book of the Twilight Saga, Bella and Edward\'s marriage brings a new set of challenges and a life-altering decision as they face an uncertain future and a powerful enemy.','book','Little, Brown and Company; Reprint edition','2008-08-02','English',768,550),(41,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/61Qs-hoZ-TL._SL1200_.jpg','The Girl with the Dragon Tattoo','Stieg Larsson',10.99,'A journalist and a troubled hacker team up to solve a decades-old disappearance in Sweden, uncovering shocking family secrets along the way.','book','Vintage Crime/Black Lizard; Reprint edition','2009-06-23','English',672,500),(42,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/91aWx6LUh-L._SL1500_.jpg','The Girl Who Played with Fire','Stieg Larsson',10.99,'Lisbeth Salander is drawn into a murder investigation involving sex trafficking and political corruption, while trying to clear her name.','book','Vintage Crime/Black Lizard; Reprint edition','2010-06-22','English',630,480),(43,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/71m-1BgkHxL._SL1500_.jpg','The Girl Who Kicked the Hornet\'s Nest','Stieg Larsson',11.99,'Lisbeth Salander must fight for her innocence and uncover the truth about her past as she faces powerful enemies and a complex conspiracy.','book','Vintage Crime/Black Lizard; Reprint edition','2011-02-22','English',820,600),(44,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/71FZo7-3BnL._SL1500_.jpg','Gone Girl','Gillian Flynn',10.99,'On their fifth wedding anniversary, Nick\'s wife Amy goes missing. As the media frenzy grows and police pressure mounts, Nick\'s portrait of a blissful union begins to crumble, revealing disturbing truths.','book','Crown Publishing Group; Reprint edition','2012-06-05','English',422,380),(45,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/71-JO+PSPwL._SL1500_.jpg','Sharp Objects','Gillian Flynn',9.99,'Reporter Camille Preaker returns to her hometown to cover a series of brutal murders, confronting her own traumatic past in the process.','book','Broadway Books; Reprint edition','2006-09-26','English',254,280),(46,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/810W+zAp2DL._SL1500_.jpg','The Martian','Andy Weir',10.99,'Stranded on Mars, astronaut Mark Watney must rely on his ingenuity and spirit to survive while NASA and his crewmates work tirelessly to bring him home.','book','Broadway Books; Reprint edition','2014-10-28','English',387,350),(47,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/81X1Czcw4mL._SL1500_.jpg','Artemis','Andy Weir',10.99,'Jazz Bashara, a porter and smuggler living in the lunar city of Artemis, becomes entangled in a conspiracy for control of the city.','book','Crown Publishing Group; Reprint edition','2017-11-14','English',320,310),(48,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/81E9oNSK3bL._SL1500_.jpg','Life of Pi','Yann Martel',9.99,'Pi Patel, a young Indian boy, survives a shipwreck and shares a lifeboat with a Bengal tiger named Richard Parker. Together, they embark on an extraordinary journey of faith and survival.','book','Mariner Books; Reprint edition','2001-09-11','English',336,310),(49,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/51M7XGLQTBL._SL1200_.jpg','The Road','Cormac McCarthy',9.99,'In a post-apocalyptic world, a father and his young son journey through a desolate landscape, struggling to survive as they move towards the coast.','book','Vintage; Reprint edition','2006-09-26','English',287,280),(50,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/51CuFc9+UWL._SL1360_.jpg','The Lovely Bones','Alice Sebold',10.99,'After being murdered, Susie Salmon watches from the afterlife as her family and friends cope with her loss and try to find her killer.','book','Little, Brown and Company; Reprint edition','2002-07-03','English',328,300),(51,_binary 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/81GUnfwsWaL._SL1500_.jpg','Big Little Lies','Liane Moriarty',10.99,'A murder at an elementary school fundraiser reveals secrets and lies among a group o